# Personal denylist — copy to `.git-personal-denylist` (gitignored) and
# add YOUR OWN values that must never be committed to this public repo.
# scripts/install-hooks.sh seeds the real file from this template; the
# pre-commit hook greps the STAGED CONTENT of your changed files for
# each line (plain substring, case-sensitive) and blocks the commit on
# a match. It scans staged content, not the diff — so a commit that
# REMOVES a denylisted value is allowed (you can clean up a past slip).
#
# One value per line. Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.
# Because the real .git-personal-denylist is gitignored, listing your
# actual values here is safe — they stay on your machine.
#
# Examples (replace with your own — these are illustrative only):
# 100.107.222.78          # my Tailscale Ollama IP
# my.real.name@email.com  # personal email
# my-laptop.local         # internal hostname
